data.event: Auburn was originally incorporated as Slaughter, Washington after Lt. William Slaughter, who died in a skirmish fighting Native Americans which are now apart of the modern day Muckleshoot tribe in 1855.

event.title: 1893, a large group of settlers from Auburn, New York, moved

data.event: In 1893, a large group of settlers from Auburn, New York, moved to Slaughter, and renamed the town to "Auburn."
